Posts.Content: PSA of 5.9, Free of 0.6, Free % of Total 10.17%=Pretty Good Chance of Prostate Cancer Or at least thats what Im reading online. I have no symptoms. Doctor took the test a couple of weeks ago. Says I should wait 2 weeks and get retested. No ejaculation for 48 prior. My PSA levels have always been in the 4.1, 4.2 range. From what Im reading online, the fact that my free percentage is 10.17% range puts me around the 55% to 60% that I have prostate cancer. I am 52 years old.
